        <para>
        During this time period there was a gradual decline in the health of
        the economies of the two Blocs as well as in actual scientific rather
        than technological knowledge growth. In addition there was a marked
        increase in religous fundamentalism in both the US and abroad in
        various Islamic and Hindu countries. Both of the superpowers of the 
        time period tended to ignore the economic build up of other countries 
        except when their own immediate well being seem threatened. Certainly 
        , both countries had a great deal to worry about.
        </para>

        <para>
        As the technological wonders mounted in number and variety, so did the
        need for energy to grow and expand. Conventional sources proved
        insufficient and standard nuclear methods proved to be to dangerous.
        During this time period public confidence in conventional
        power sources was on the decline. 
        </para>

        <para>
        The stresses placed on some of the smaller countries by the three ``super powers''
        (EEC,Soviet Union, USA) caused many of the countries to form serious coalitions
        with similiarly inclined republics. Thus came into being the United Islamic States,
        sthe Indos Island States (Phillipines and Indonesia), and the loosley allied 
        Scandinavian Coalition (the Scandic).
        </para>

        <para>
        Multinational Corporations became commonplace as each country's industrial 
        complex bought into the financial structure of several others. Space travel 
        was almost an ignored project with only small bits of developement going on 
        at a relatively low intensity . 
        </para>

        <para>
        Other methods of energy production became standard. With the 
        discovery of a highly efficient technique for solar energy conversion 
        came an increased traffic flow between the planet and its moon.
        </para>

        <para>
        The smaller countries begin to use the U.N. as a fairly sophisticated 
        lever against both of the two super powers. The EEC, Israel, the 
        Islamic state coalition, and the republic of India are primary 
        supporters. in doing so they establish a fairly strong tradition for 
        the U.N. as a military force and the use of Israeli Officers as advisors. 
        </para>

        <para>
        Unrest over food shortages continued. in addition there was
        a slight resurgence of territoriality within the
        northwestern hemisphere.
        </para>

        <para>
        A small group of dedicated visionaries succeeded in secretly
        launching a colony ship from the sirius orbital station. the
        "Gang of l-5" was tried and convicted of treason. later
        pardoned as a result of public outcry.
        </para>

        <para>
        Exploration increased rapidly. all planets except Saturn and
        Jupiter are successfully landed upon.
        </para>

        <para>
        United Nations Standard units of Exchange become a standard 
        media of exchange for all but NorAm Combine and the Soviet Union. 
        </para>

        <para>
        Resource tensions cause the first major conflict of the 21st century, 
        the Brushfire war, which lasts for all of 13 days and renders goodly 
        portions of Somalia and the United Islamic Coordinate unihabitable. 
        The Iraqi valley oil fields are made useless by heavy fallout.   
        </para>

        <para>
        In the year 2046 a the lunar colony selene discovers the
        presence of a space craft landing site - over 2000 years
        old.
        </para>

        <para>
        In the early part of the 2050s there comes a long series of 
        conflicts in the middle European and South American arena 
        that feature major losses for each of the two super powers.
        </para>

        <para>
        During this time period the incarcerations begin. hundreds of thousands of 
        North American citizens are jailed for Un-American and Un-Canadian stances.
        "Proctors" become become overseers of public education. 
        </para>

        <para>
        World economic conditions worsen.
        </para>

        <para>
        The North American States experience the first net emigration of people 
        in two centuries.
        </para>

        <para>
        The Soviet Union switches over to the U.N. Standard of exchange and 
        agrees to adhere to U.N. Resource management restrictions. The 
        founder of Jackl Power Inc. , suffering from a terminal illness, 
        wills his fortune, his entire stock holding in Jackl Power (74\%) , 
        and his land holdings in upper New York State to the Mohawk Nation of 
        Quebec. The Mohawk Nation uses the money to finance the building of 
        the ``Red Jacket University of Power Engineering ''. In addition, 
        they begin one of the largest public relations campaigns in history 
        as part of an attempt to separate from the NorAm combine. 
        </para>

